<font color="#FF0000">MY HEART</font><br>
<tt>Sat Feb  8 23:45:38 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
This is my first time to see this site. Therefore,<br>
I have no feel for what this is really all about. I<br>
admit that up front. My first impression is that <br>
somehow a small group of people are enjoying some<br>
kind of intellectual game about Nam, Protestors, the<br>
Vets, and a series of overlapping generations.<br><br>
Vietnam Vets are not differentiated by their state<br>
of mind or their existence in '66, '68, or '72. We are<br>
different now because of our experience then. I am<br>
a Vet. I was as in tune with the evolution of our<br>
youth into change as anyone. I just lost a year &amp;<br>
a half of perspective of that relationship, and logged<br>
a year of bewilderment.<br><br>
When we came home, the experience was as varied as the<br>
one we all got in Nam. But there was a bottom line<br>
differnce for us. My very own generation didn't have<br>
enough respect for its own to care. Bottom line.<br><br>
We, the self styled free thinking generation, were<br>
guilty of the most base of neglect. Nam Vets needed<br>
support. We gave as much of our souls to Nam as those<br>
who protested gave. Talk to a Vet that was there in<br>
1967 compared to one there in 1971. The demand on us<br>
was very different. Talk to a protestor from either<br>
period, and they are the same.<br><br>
I only know one thing. For thirty odd years, I haven't<br>
slept well. I have Buddies who died there, and Buddies<br>
who waited to come here to die from it. I wonder about<br>
what I did and why. I am always willing to try to figure<br>
it out. I've never met one who was a protestor who really<br>
gives a big shit about it. Even the one's who tore my<br>
heart out at Kent State don't seem to realize that what<br>
happened to them on one dark day, lives in us in a<br>
dizzying array of memories.<br><br>
I don't hate those who didn't serve. I could give a shit.<br>
Hell, when those draft notices were being mailed, only<br>
an idiot couldn't figure out where you were headed.<br><br>
Respect. A little help for those in the VA units. How<br>
about someone who doesn't ask how many you got to kill.<br>
Christ, are we the most enlightened generation or the<br>
most selfish. <br><br>
Back off on this discussion some. Get back to some real<br>
issues. Unless those who talk here are into some kind of<br>
political science project, try to reach out to the real<br>
impact on Americans that the Nam was.<br><br>
I don't hate nobody. I just want a good nights sleep.<br><br>
Love and Peace Man.
<p><code>-- carnival@ont.com  (JJ the Boonirat) </code><p>


